comment: Lopez (BKN) extends his arms as he sets the screen on Brewer (HOU) without giving him room to avoid the contact.

Beverley (HOU) cleanly strips the ball from Lopez (BKN).
Lopez (BKN) sets the screen on Brewer (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Brewer (HOU) makes contact with Johnson's (BKN) body that affects his shot attempt.

As Jack (BKN) comes to defend Brewer (HOU) and makes incidental contact, Brewer spins away and travels. The official’s primary focus is the contact, and he doesn’t pick up the illegal pivot movement.
Terry (HOU) starts the drive outside the LBD. Lopez (BKN) is the secondary defender and on the floor in the RA when contact occurs, so Terry's shooting motion cannot be deemed unnatural.
